<br>
3. Don't talk to a warrior about mob positioning, he's one of 6 people in an average group, and is *generally* not the one who's responsible for mobs being placed out of position, it's almost always others who are attacking from one of the flanks that is.   Kicks and Bashes give more mob movement than standard attacking will.  Any angular kick or bash will move the mob out of position, and your moronic pet who has backstab but is incapable of actually aiming for the back will suffer as a result about this.   <br>
<br>
4. I use Norge`Tal so that YOU don't die, it moves mobs.   It moves them a LOT and your pet will lose his position, deal with it, it's a fact of life, if you prefer, i can use one of my lower aggro weapons and you can die a few times, but I think that my aggro is far more important than your pet being able to backstab a couple of times.<br>
<br>
